==English==
[[Image:A fair Puritan.png|thumb|150px|right|A woman holding [[holly]] in her apron.]]

===Etymology===
Earlier {{term|napron}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|napperon}}, diminutive of {{term|nappe||tablecloth}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|nappa||napkin}}. The phrase ''a napron'' was reinterpreted as ''an apron'', that is why the initial ''n'' is now missing.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈeɪ.pɹən/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"eI.pr@n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-apron.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# An article of [[clothing]] worn over the front of the [[torso]] and/or [[legs]] for protection from [[spill]]s.
# A hard surface bordering a structure or area.
## The paved area of an [[airport]].
## The spreading end of a [[driveway]].
## The paved area below the [[yellow]] line on a [[race track]].
## The portion of a [[stage]] extending towards the [[audience]] beyond the [[proscenium arch]] in a [[theatre]].
# The sides of a tree’s [[canopy]].

